            "content": "# Clap Subcommands Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Restructure the client binary with clap subcommands so `reme export` / `reme import` can be added later, while preserving backward compatibility (`reme` = TUI).\n\n**Architecture:** Split the existing flat `CliArgs` into a `Cli` struct with `Option<Commands>` subcommand enum. Global args (data_dir, config, log_level) live on `Cli`. TUI-specific args move into `TuiArgs`. Export/Import are stubs that print \"not implemented\" and exit. The `load_config()` function is split into `load_global_config()` (used by all subcommands) and TUI-specific config merging.\n\n**Tech Stack:** clap (already in Cargo.toml), Rust\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Define the new CLI struct hierarchy in config.rs\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/config.rs:56-146` (replace `CliArgs` with `Cli`, `Commands`, `TuiArgs`, `ExportArgs`, `ImportArgs`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test — subcommand parsing**\n\nAdd to the `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` block in `apps/client/src/config.rs`:\n\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn test_cli_no_subcommand_defaults_to_none() {\n    use clap::Parser;\n    let cli = Cli::try_parse_from([\"reme\"]).unwrap();\n    assert!(cli.command.is_none());\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn test_cli_tui_subcommand() {\n    use clap::Parser;\n    let cli = Cli::try_parse_from([\"reme\", \"tui\"]).unwrap();\n    assert!(matches!(cli.command, Some(Commands::Tui(_))));\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn test_cli_export_subcommand_stub() {\n    use clap::Parser;\n    let cli = Cli::try_parse_from([\"reme\", \"export\", \"out.reme\"]).unwrap();\n    match cli.command {\n        Some(Commands::Export(args)) => {\n            assert_eq!(args.file, PathBuf::from(\"out.reme\"));\n        }\n        _ => panic!(\"Expected Export subcommand\"),\n    }\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn test_cli_import_subcommand_stub() {\n    use clap::Parser;\n    let cli = Cli::try_parse_from([\"reme\", \"import\", \"in.reme\"]).unwrap();\n    match cli.command {\n        Some(Commands::Import(args)) => {\n            assert_eq!(args.file, PathBuf::from(\"in.reme\"));\n        }\n        _ => panic!(\"Expected Import subcommand\"),\n    }\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn test_cli_global_args_with_subcommand() {\n    use clap::Parser;\n    let cli = Cli::try_parse_from([\n        \"reme\",\n        \"--data-dir\", \"/tmp/test\",\n        \"--log-level\", \"debug\",\n        \"tui\",\n    ]).unwrap();\n    assert_eq!(cli.data_dir, Some(PathBuf::from(\"/tmp/test\")));\n    assert_eq!(cli.log_level, Some(\"debug\".to_string()));\n    assert!(matches!(cli.command, Some(Commands::Tui(_))));\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn test_cli_global_args_without_subcommand() {\n    use clap::Parser;\n    let cli = Cli::try_parse_from([\n        \"reme\",\n        \"--data-dir\", \"/tmp/test\",\n    ]).unwrap();\n    assert_eq!(cli.data_dir, Some(PathBuf::from(\"/tmp/test\")));\n    assert!(cli.command.is_none());\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn test_cli_tui_specific_args() {\n    use clap::Parser;\n    let cli = Cli::try_parse_from([\n        \"reme\", \"tui\",\n        \"--http-url\", \"https://node:23003\",\n        \"--embedded-node\",\n    ]).unwrap();\n    match cli.command {\n        Some(Commands::Tui(args)) => {\n            assert_eq!(args.http_url, Some(vec![\"https://node:23003\".to_string()]));\n            assert!(args.embedded_node);\n        }\n        _ => panic!(\"Expected Tui subcommand\"),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client -- test_cli_no_subcommand`\nExpected: FAIL — `Cli` struct doesn't exist yet\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Replace `CliArgs` with the new CLI hierarchy**\n\nReplace the `CliArgs` struct (lines 56-146 of `config.rs`) with:\n\n```rust\n/// Top-level CLI arguments\n#[derive(Parser, Debug, Clone)]\n#[command(name = \"reme\")]\n#[command(author, version, about = \"Resilient Messenger\")]\npub struct Cli {\n    #[command(subcommand)]\n    pub command: Option<Commands>,\n\n    /// Directory for storing identity, keys, and messages\n    #[arg(short = 'd', long, env = \"REME_DATA_DIR\")]\n    pub data_dir: Option<PathBuf>,\n\n    /// Path to config file (default: ~/.config/reme/config.toml)\n    #[arg(short = 'c', long, env = \"REME_CONFIG\")]\n    pub config: Option<PathBuf>,\n\n    /// Log level (trace, debug, info, warn, error)\n    #[arg(short = 'l', long, env = \"REME_LOG_LEVEL\")]\n    pub log_level: Option<String>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Subcommand, Debug, Clone)]\npub enum Commands {\n    /// Launch the interactive TUI (default when no subcommand given)\n    Tui(TuiArgs),\n    /// Export pending messages to a .reme bundle file\n    Export(ExportArgs),\n    /// Import messages from a .reme bundle file\n    Import(ImportArgs),\n}\n\n/// TUI-specific arguments (transport, outbox, embedded node)\n#[derive(Parser, Debug, Clone, Serialize)]\npub struct TuiArgs {\n    /// HTTP endpoint URLs (pair with --http-cert-pin by order)\n    #[arg(long, value_delimiter = ',')]\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    pub http_url: Option<Vec<String>>,\n\n    /// Certificate pins for HTTP endpoints\n    #[arg(long, value_delimiter = ',')]\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    pub http_cert_pin: Option<Vec<String>>,\n\n    /// MQTT broker URLs\n    #[arg(long, value_delimiter = ',')]\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    pub mqtt_url: Option<Vec<String>>,\n\n    /// Client IDs for MQTT brokers\n    #[arg(long, value_delimiter = ',')]\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    pub mqtt_client_id: Option<Vec<String>>,\n\n    /// Outbox retry check interval in seconds\n    #[arg(long, env = \"REME_OUTBOX_TICK_INTERVAL\")]\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    pub outbox_tick_inte