            "content": "# `reme export` Command Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Implement `reme export` CLI subcommand that exports pending outbox messages to a `.reme` bundle file.\n\n**Architecture:** Read-only offline operation. Opens Storage directly, queries outbox, applies filters, encodes each message as WirePayload frame, writes through BundleWriter. No network, no Client, no transport. New `export.rs` module in the client app.\n\n**Tech Stack:** reme-storage, reme-outbox, reme-message (WirePayload), reme-bundle (BundleWriter), reme-identity (PublicID), humantime (duration parsing), clap (CLI args)\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add `humantime` dependency to workspace and client\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `Cargo.toml` (workspace root)\n- Modify: `apps/client/Cargo.toml`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add humantime to workspace dependencies**\n\nIn root `Cargo.toml`, add to `[workspace.dependencies]` section (alphabetical order, near `hex`):\n\n```toml\nhumantime = \"2\"\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Add humantime to client dependencies**\n\nIn `apps/client/Cargo.toml`, add under the `# config` section:\n\n```toml\nhumantime = { workspace = true }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify it compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p client`\nExpected: Compiles cleanly\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add Cargo.toml apps/client/Cargo.toml\ngit commit -m \"chore: add humantime dependency for duration parsing\n\nRef: #157\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Add `outbox_get_all` and `outbox_get_all_for_recipient` to OutboxStore trait\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/reme-outbox/src/store.rs` (trait + Arc blanket impl)\n- Modify: `crates/reme-storage/src/lib.rs` (Storage impl)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add methods to `OutboxStore` trait**\n\nIn `crates/reme-outbox/src/store.rs`, add after `outbox_get_for_recipient` (line 39):\n\n```rust\n    /// Get all outbox entries including confirmed and expired.\n    ///\n    /// Used by export with `--include-sent` to re-export confirmed messages.\n    fn outbox_get_all(&self) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error>;\n\n    /// Get all outbox entries for a specific recipient including confirmed and expired.\n    fn outbox_get_all_for_recipient(\n        &self,\n        recipient: &PublicID,\n    ) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error>;\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Add Arc blanket impl for both methods**\n\nIn the same file, inside `impl<T: OutboxStore> OutboxStore for Arc<T>`, add:\n\n```rust\n    fn outbox_get_all(&self) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error> {\n        (**self).outbox_get_all()\n    }\n\n    fn outbox_get_all_for_recipient(\n        &self,\n        recipient: &PublicID,\n    ) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error> {\n        (**self).outbox_get_all_for_recipient(recipient)\n    }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement in Storage**\n\nIn `crates/reme-storage/src/lib.rs`, add after the `outbox_get_for_recipient` implementation (after line ~1429). The SQL is the same as `outbox_get_pending`/`outbox_get_for_recipient` but WITHOUT the `confirmed_at_ms IS NULL AND expired_at_ms IS NULL` filter, and with `expired_at_ms` added to the SELECT:\n\n```rust\n    fn outbox_get_all(&self) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error> {\n        let conn = self.conn.lock().map_err(|_| StorageError::LockPoisoned)?;\n        let mut stmt = conn.prepare(\n            \"SELECT message_id, recipient_id, content_id, envelope_bytes, inner_bytes,\n                    created_at_ms, expires_at_ms, expired_at_ms, next_retry_at_ms,\n                    confirmation_type, confirmation_data\n             FROM outbox\n             ORDER BY created_at_ms ASC\",\n        )?;\n\n        let rows = stmt.query_map([], |row| {\n            Ok((\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(0)?,         // message_id\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(1)?,         // recipient_id\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(2)?,         // content_id\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(3)?,         // envelope_bytes\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(4)?,         // inner_bytes\n                row.get::<_, u64>(5)?,             // created_at_ms\n                row.get::<_, Option<u64>>(6)?,     // expires_at_ms\n                row.get::<_, Option<u64>>(7)?,     // expired_at_ms\n                row.get::<_, Option<u64>>(8)?,     // next_retry_at_ms\n                row.get::<_, Option<String>>(9)?,  // confirmation_type\n                row.get::<_, Option<Vec<u8>>>(10)?, // confirmation_data\n            ))\n        })?;\n\n        let mut messages = Vec::new();\n        for row in rows {\n            let (\n                message_id, recipient_id, content_id, envelope_bytes, inner_bytes,\n                created_at_ms, expires_at_ms, expired_at_ms, next_retry_at_ms,\n                confirmation_type, confirmation_data,\n            ) = row?;\n\n            messages.push(Self::load_pending_message(\n                &conn, message_id, recipient_id, content_id, envelope_bytes, inner_bytes,\n                created_at_ms, expires_at_ms, expired_at_ms, next_retry_at_ms,\n                confirmation_type, confirmation_data,\n            )?);\n        }\n\n        Ok(messages)\n    }\n\n    fn outbox_get_all_for_recipient(\n        &self,\n        recipient: &PublicID,\n    ) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error> {\n        let recipient_bytes = recipient.to_bytes();\n\n        let conn = self.conn.lock().map_err(|_| StorageError::LockPoisoned)?;\n        let mut stmt = conn.prepare(\n            \"SELECT message_id, recipient_id, content_id, envelope_bytes, inner_bytes,\n                    created_at_ms, expires_at_ms, expired_at_ms, next_retry_at_ms,\n                    confirmation_type, confirmation_data\n             FROM outbox\n             WHERE recipient_id = ?\n             ORDER BY created_at_ms ASC\",\n        )?;\n\n        let rows = stmt.query_map(params![&recipient_bytes[..]], |row| {\n            Ok((\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(0)?,\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(1)?,\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(2)?,\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(3)?,\n                row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(4)?,\n                row.get::<_, u64>(5)?,\n                row.get::<_, Option<u64>>(6)?,\n                row.get::<_, Option<u64>>(7)?,\n                row.get::<_, Option<u64>>(8)?,\n                row.get::<_, Option<String>>(9)?,\n                row.get::<_, Option<Vec<u8>>>(10)?,\n            ))\n        })?;\n\n        let mut messages = Vec::new();\n        for row in rows {\n            let (\n                message_id, recipient_id, content_id, envelope_bytes, inner_bytes,\n                created_at_ms, expires_at_ms, expired_at_ms, next_retry_at_ms,\n                confirmation_type, confirmation_data,\n            ) = row?;\n\n            messages.push(Self::load_pending_message(\n                &conn, message_id, recipient_id, content_id, envelope_bytes, inner_bytes,\n                created_at_ms, expires_at_ms, expired_at_ms, next_retry_at_ms,\n                confirmation_type, confirmation_data,\n            )?);\n        }\n\n        Ok(messages)\n    }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Add to MockOutboxStore in outbox tests**\n\nIn `crates/reme-outbox/src/lib.rs`, inside the `impl OutboxStore for MockOutboxStore` block, add:\n\n```rust\n        fn outbox_get_all(&self) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error> {\n            Ok(self.entries.borrow().values().cloned().collect())\n        }\n\n        fn outbox_get_all_for_recipient(\n            &self,\n            recipient: &PublicID,\n        ) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, Self::Error> {\n            Ok(self\n                .entries\n                .borrow()\n                .values()\n                .filter(|m| m.recipient == *recip