            "content": "# `reme import` CLI Subcommand — Design Spec\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28\n**Issue:** #158\n**Milestone:** v0.5 — Sneakernet Export\n\n---\n\n## Goal\n\nImport messages from a `.reme` bundle file. v0.5 scope: self-addressed messages only. Messages for other routing keys are skipped with a warning.\n\n## CLI Interface\n\n```text\nreme import <FILE>\n\nArguments:\n  <FILE>  Path to a .reme bundle file to import\n```\n\nNo additional flags for v0.5. The command is idempotent — re-importing the same bundle skips duplicates silently.\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe import command needs `Client` (for `process_message_local` which handles decryption, storage, DAG updates, and dedup). It also needs identity loading (for decryption) and a no-op transport (since `Client::new` requires `Arc<T: Transport>` but import never sends anything).\n\n### File layout\n\n- `apps/client/src/import.rs` — import logic, no-op transport, identity loading\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/main.rs` — wire import subcommand\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `reme-bundle` — `BundleReader`\n- `reme-core` — `Client`, `ClientError`\n- `reme-message` — `WirePayload`, `OuterEnvelope`\n- `reme-identity` — `Identity`, `is_encrypted`, `load_identity`\n- `reme-storage` — `Storage`\n- `reme-transport` — `Transport` trait (for no-op impl)\n\n## Data Flow\n\n1. Load identity from `data_dir/identity.reme` (prompt for password if encrypted)\n2. Open `Storage::open(data_dir/messages.db)`\n3. Create `Client::new(identity, Arc::new(NoopTransport), storage)` — no-op transport since import is offline\n4. Open bundle via `BundleReader::open(File::open(path)?)`\n5. Read all frames, then verify checksum\n6. For each frame:\n   - `WirePayload::decode(&frame)` — determine type\n   - `WirePayload::Message(envelope)`:\n     - Call `client.process_message_local(&envelope)`\n     - On success → count as imported\n     - On `ClientError::WrongRecipient` → count as skipped (not for us)\n     - On `ClientError::DuplicateMessage` → count as duplicate\n     - On other error → log warning, continue\n   - `WirePayload::AckTombstone(_)`:\n     - Skip for v0.5 (no client-side tombstone processing exists)\n     - Count as skipped tombstone\n   - Unknown variant → skip with warning (forward compat)\n7. Print summary to stderr: `Imported N messages (M skipped as not for us, D duplicates, T tombstones skipped)`\n\n## No-op Transport\n\nMinimal implementation for `Client` construction:\n\n```rust\nstruct NoopTransport;\n\nimpl Transport for NoopTransport {\n    async fn submit_message(&self, _: OuterEnvelope) -> Result<(), TransportError> { Ok(()) }\n    async fn submit_ack_tombstone(&self, _: SignedAckTombstone) -> Result<(), TransportError> { Ok(()) }\n}\n```\n\n## Deduplication\n\nHandled automatically by `process_message_local` — the `messages` table has a `UNIQUE` constraint on `message_id`. Duplicates produce `StorageError::AlreadyExists` which `process_message_local` maps to a benign duplicate detection path. Import counts these and skips.\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n- Corrupt bundle → error with context\n- No identity file → error: \"No identity found. Run `reme` first to create one.\"\n- Empty bundle → \"Nothing to import\", exit 0\n- All messages for other identities → \"No messages for this identity\", exit 0\n- Encrypted identity → password prompt (reuse `tui::password::prompt_for_password`)\n\n## Tombstones\n\n**Skipped for v0.5.** No client-side `process_tombstone` method exists. Tombstone frames in the bundle are counted and reported in the summary but not processed. The relay node handles tombstone processing when messages are submitted via the node import path.\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Integration test**: create messages via `Client` for identity A, export to bundle, create a separate storage for identity A, import bundle, verify messages appear in storage\n- **Dedup test**: import same bundle twice, verify no duplicate messages\n- **Wrong recipient test**: bundle with messages for identity B, import as identity A, verify all skipped\n- **Mixed test**: bundle with messages for A and B, import as A, verify only A's messages imported\n",
