            "content": "# `reme import` Command Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Implement `reme import` CLI subcommand that imports messages from a `.reme` bundle file, including a refactor to extract shared identity loading logic.\n\n**Architecture:** Two-part change: (1) Extract identity loading from `tui/mod.rs` into shared `identity.rs` module. (2) Import command opens bundle, decodes frames, uses `Client::process_message_local` for decryption/storage/dedup. No-op transport since import is offline. Messages for other routing keys are skipped.\n\n**Tech Stack:** reme-bundle (BundleReader), reme-core (Client), reme-message (WirePayload), reme-identity, reme-storage, reme-transport (Transport trait for NoopTransport)\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Extract identity module from TUI\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `apps/client/src/identity.rs`\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/tui/mod.rs` — remove identity functions, delegate to new module\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/tui/password.rs` — remove (content moves to identity.rs)\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/main.rs` — add `mod identity;`\n\nThe goal is to move `setup_identity`, `load_existing_identity`, `create_new_identity`, and `prompt_for_password` into a new `apps/client/src/identity.rs` module that is usable by both TUI and CLI subcommands.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Create `identity.rs` with the extracted functions**\n\nCreate `apps/client/src/identity.rs`. Move the functions from `tui/mod.rs` (lines 60-152) and `tui/password.rs` (the `prompt_for_password` function) into this new module. The public API should be:\n\n```rust\n//! Identity management: loading, creating, and password-protected identities.\n\nuse reme_identity::{is_encrypted, load_identity, save_identity, EncryptedIdentityError, Identity};\nuse std::fs;\nuse std::io::{self, Write};\nuse std::path::Path;\nuse zeroize::Zeroizing;\n\n/// Load an existing identity or create a new one interactively.\n///\n/// Used by the TUI on startup. If the file doesn't exist, prompts the user\n/// to create a new identity with optional password protection.\npub fn load_or_create(identity_path: &Path) -> Result<Identity, Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    if !identity_path.exists() {\n        return create_new(identity_path);\n    }\n    load_existing(identity_path)\n}\n\n/// Load an existing identity file, prompting for password if encrypted.\n///\n/// Returns an error if the identity file doesn't exist.\n/// Used by CLI subcommands (import, etc.) that require an identity but\n/// should not create one.\npub fn load_existing(identity_path: &Path) -> Result<Identity, Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    let data = fs::read(identity_path)?;\n\n    if !is_encrypted(&data) {\n        return load_identity(&data, None)\n            .map_err(|e| format!(\"Failed to load identity: {e}\").into());\n    }\n\n    // Encrypted - prompt for password\n    println!();\n    println!(\"========================================\");\n    println!(\"  Identity file is password-protected\");\n    println!(\"========================================\");\n    println!();\n    io::stdout().flush()?;\n\n    loop {\n        let password = Zeroizing::new(prompt_for_password(\"Enter password: \")?);\n        match load_identity(&data, Some(password.as_bytes())) {\n            Ok(identity) => {\n                println!();\n                return Ok(identity);\n            }\n            Err(EncryptedIdentityError::DecryptionFailed) => {\n                println!(\"Wrong password. Try again (or press Ctrl+C to exit).\");\n                println!();\n            }\n            Err(e) => {\n                return Err(format!(\"Failed to load identity: {e}\").into());\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/// Prompt for a password without echoing characters.\npub fn prompt_for_password(prompt: &str) -> io::Result<String> {\n    rpassword::prompt_password(prompt)\n}\n\n/// Create a new identity interactively with optional password protection.\nfn create_new(identity_path: &Path) -> Result<Identity, Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    // (exact copy of create_new_identity from tui/mod.rs lines 107-152)\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nCopy the `create_new_identity` body from `tui/mod.rs` lines 107-152 into the `create_new` function. Adapt error types from `AppResult<Identity>` to `Result<Identity, Box<dyn std::error::Error>>`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update `tui/mod.rs` to use the new identity module**\n\nReplace the identity functions in `tui/mod.rs` with delegation to `crate::identity`:\n\n```rust\nuse crate::identity;\n\npub async fn run(config: AppConfig) -> AppResult<()> {\n    fs::create_dir_all(&config.data_dir)?;\n\n    let identity_path = config.data_dir.join(\"identity.reme\");\n    let identity = identity::load_or_create(&identity_path)?;\n\n    // ... rest unchanged\n}\n```\n\nRemove `setup_identity`, `load_existing_identity`, `create_new_identity` from `tui/mod.rs`.\nRemove imports: `password::prompt_for_password`, `reme_identity::{is_encrypted, load_identity, save_identity, EncryptedIdentityError}`, `zeroize::Zeroizing`.\nRemove `use std::io::{self, Write}` if no longer needed.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Remove `tui/password.rs`**\n\nDelete `apps/client/src/tui/password.rs`. Remove `mod password;` from `tui/mod.rs`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Add `mod identity;` to `main.rs`**\n\nAdd `mod identity;` declaration in `apps/client/src/main.rs` after `mod export;`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Verify everything compiles and tests pass**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p client`\nExpected: All existing tests pass (identity behavior unchanged)\n\nRun: `cargo clippy -p client --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\nExpected: Clean\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/identity.rs apps/client/src/tui/mod.rs apps/client/src/main.rs\ngit rm apps/client/src/tui/password.rs\ngit commit -m \"refactor: extract identity module from TUI for shared use\n\nMove setup_identity, load_existing_identity, create_new_identity, and\nprompt_for_password into apps/client/src/identity.rs. TUI delegates to\nthe shared module. Enables import and other CLI subcommands to load\nidentity without depending on TUI internals.\n\nRef: #158\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Implement the import module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `apps/client/src/import.rs`\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/main.rs` — wire import subcommand\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Create `import.rs`**\n\nCreate `apps/client/src/import.rs`:\n\n```rust\n//! Import messages from a `.reme` bundle file.\n//!\n//! Reads a bundle, decodes each frame, and processes self-addressed messages\n//! via `Client::process_message_local`. Messages for other routing keys are\n//! skipped. Duplicate messages are silently ignored (idempotent import).\n\nuse crate::config::{AppConfig, ImportArgs};\nuse reme_bundle::BundleReader;\nuse reme_core::{Client, ClientError};\nuse reme_message::wire::WirePayload;\nuse reme_message::OuterEnvelope;\nuse reme_message::tombstone::SignedAckTombstone;\nuse reme_storage::Storage;\nuse reme_transport::{Transport, TransportError};\nuse std::fs::File;\nuse std::sync::Arc;\n\n/// No-op transport for offline import (Client requires a transport but import never sends).\nstruct NoopTransport;\n\n#[async_trait::async_trait]\nimpl Transport for NoopTransport {\n    async fn submit_message(&self, _: OuterEnvelope) -> Result<(), TransportError> {\n        Ok(())\n    }\n    async fn submit_ack_tombstone(&self, _: SignedAckTombstone) -> Result<(), TransportError> {\n        Ok(())\n    }\n}\n\n/// Import summary counters.\nstruct ImportSummary {\n    imported: usize,\n    duplicates: usize,\n    skipped_not_for_us: usize,\n    skipped_tombstones: usize,\n    errors: usize,\n}\n\n/// Run the import subcommand.\npub fn run_import(config: &AppConfig, args: &ImportArgs) -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    // Check input file exists\n    if !args.file.exists() {\n        return Err(format!(\"Bundle file '{}' not found.\", args.file.display()).into());\n    }\n\n    // Load identity\n    let identity_path = config.data_dir.join(\"identity.reme\");\n    if !identity_path.exists() {\n        return Err(\"No identity found. Run `reme` first to create one.\".into());\n    }\n    let identity = crate::identity::load_existing(&identity_path)?;\n\n    // Open storage\n    let db_path = config.data_dir.join(\"messages.db\");\n    let storage = Storage::open(\n        db_path.to_str().ok_or(\"Invalid database path (non-UTF8)\")?,\n    )?;\n\n    // Create client with no-op transport (offline import)\n    let client = Client::new(identity, Arc::new(NoopTransport), storage);\n\n    // Read and verify bundle\n    let frames = read_bundle(&args.file)?;\n\n    if frames.is_empty() {\n        eprintln!(\"Nothing to import (empty bundle).\");\n        return Ok(());\n    }\n\n    // Process each frame\n    let summary = process_frames(&client, &frames);\n\n    // Print summary\n    print_summary(&summary);\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n\n/// Read all frames from a bundle file and verify checksum.\nfn read_bundle(path: &std::path::Path) -> Result<Vec<Vec<u8>>, Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    let file = File::open(path)?;\n    let mut reader = BundleReader::open(file)?;\n\n    let mut frames = Vec::with_capacity(reader.frame_count() as usize);\n    while let Some(frame) = reader.next_frame()? {\n        frames.push(frame);\n    }\n\n    reader.verify_checksum()?;\n    Ok(frames)\n}\n\n/// Process decoded frames through the client.\nfn process_frames<T: Transport>(client: &Client<T>, frames: &[Vec<u8>]) -> ImportSummary {\n    let mut summary = ImportSummary {\n        imported: 0,\n        duplicates: 0,\n        skipped_not_for_us: 0,\n        skipped_tombstones: 0,\n        errors: 0,\n    };\n\n    for (i, frame) in frames.iter().enumerate() {\n        match WirePayload::decode(frame) {\n            Ok(WirePayload::Message(envelope)) => {\n                process_message(client, &envelope, i, &mut summary);\n            }\n            Ok(WirePayload::AckTombstone(_)) => {\n                summary.skipped_tombstones += 1;\n            }\n            Err(e) => {\n                eprintln!(\"Warning: frame {i}: failed to decode WirePayload: {e}\");\n                summary.errors += 1;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    summary\n}\n\n/// Process a single message envelope.\nfn process_message<T: Transport>(\n    client: &Client<T>,\n    envelope: &OuterEnvelope,\n    frame_index: usize,\n    summary: &mut ImportSummary,\n) {\n    match client.process_message_local(envelope) {\n        Ok(_processed) => {\n            // process_message_local succeeds for both new and duplicate messages\n            // (duplicates are handled idempotently inside)\n            summary.imported += 1;\n        }\n        Err(ClientError::WrongRecipient) => {\n            summary.skipped_not_for_us += 1;\n        }\n        Err(ClientError::ConflictingDuplicate(id)) => {\n            eprintln!(\n                \"Warning: frame {frame_index}: conflicting duplicate for message {}\",\n                hex::encode(id.as_bytes())\n            );\n            summary.duplicates += 1;\n        }\n        Err(e) => {\n            eprintln!(\"Warning: frame {frame_index}: {e}\");\n            summary.errors += 1;\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/// Print the import summary to stderr.\nfn print_summary(s: &ImportSummary) {\n    let total = s.imported + s.duplicates + s.skipped_not_for_us + s.skipped_tombstones + s.errors;\n\n    if s.imported == 0 && s.duplicates == 0 {\n        eprintln!(\"No messages for this identity ({total} frames processed).\");\n        return;\n    }\n\n    let mut parts = vec![format!(\"{} imported\", s.imported)];\n    if s.duplicates > 0 {\n        parts.push(format!(\"{} duplicates\", s.duplicates));\n    }\n    if s.skipped_not_for_us > 0 {\n        parts.push(format!(\"{} not for us\", s.skipped_not_for_us));\n    }\n    if s.skipped_tombstones > 0 {\n        parts.push(format!(\"{} tombstones skipped\", s.skipped_tombstones));\n    }\n    if s.errors > 0 {\n        parts.push(format!(\"{} errors\", s.errors));\n    }\n    eprintln!(\"Import complete: {}\", parts.join(\", \"));\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n    use reme_bundle::BundleWriter;\n    use reme_identity::Identity;\n    use reme_message::OuterEnvelope;\n    use std::io::Cursor;\n\n    fn make_test_envelope(identity: &Identity) -> OuterEnvelope {\n        let routing_key = identity.public_id().routing_key();\n        OuterEnvelope::new(\n            routing_key,\n            None,\n            [0u8; 32],\n            [0u8; 16],\n            vec![0u8; 64],\n        )\n    }\n\n    fn make_bundle_bytes(envelopes: &[&OuterEnvelope]) -> Vec<u8> {\n        let mut buf = Vec::new();\n        let mut writer = BundleWriter::new(&mut buf);\n        for env in envelopes {\n            let wire = WirePayload::Message((*env).clone());\n            let frame = wire.encode().unwrap();\n            writer.write_frame(&frame).unwrap();\n        }\n        writer.finish().unwrap();\n        buf\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_read_bundle_and_verify() {\n        let alice = Identity::generate();\n        let env = make_test_envelope(&alice);\n        let bundle = make_bundle_bytes(&[&env]);\n\n        let frames = {\n            let mut reader = BundleReader::open(Cursor::new(&bundle)).unwrap();\n            let mut frames = Vec::new();\n            while let Some(f) = reader.next_frame().unwrap() {\n                frames.push(f);\n            }\n            reader.verify_checksum().unwrap();\n            frames\n        };\n\n        assert_eq!(frames.len(), 1);\n        let payload = WirePayload::decode(&frames[0]).unwrap();\n        assert!(matches!(payload, WirePayload::Message(_)));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_import_self_addressed_messages() {\n        let alice = Identity::generate();\n        let env1 = make_test_envelope(&alice);\n        let env2 = make_test_envelope(&alice);\n\n        let storage = Storage::open(\":memory:\").unwrap();\n        let client = Client::new(alice, Arc::new(NoopTransport), storage);\n\n        let frames_data = make_bundle_bytes(&[&env1, &env2]);\n        let mut reader = BundleReader::open(Cursor::new(&frames_data)).unwrap();\n        let mut frames = Vec::new();\n        while let Some(f) = reader.next_frame().unwrap() {\n            frames.push(f);\n        }\n\n        let summary = process_frames(&client, &frames);\n        // These are dummy envelopes with zero ephemeral key — decryption will fail\n        // but the routing key check passes, so they count as errors not \"not for us\"\n        assert_eq!(summary.skipped_not_for_us, 0);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_import_wrong_recipient_skipped() {\n        let alice = Identity::generate();\n        let bob = Identity::generate();\n\n        // Create envelope for bob\n        let env = make_test_envelope(&bob);\n\n        let storage = Storage::open(\":memory:\").unwrap();\n        let client = Client::new(alice, Arc::new(NoopTransport), storage);\n\n        let frames_data = make_bundle_bytes(&[&env]);\n        let mut reader = BundleReader::open(Cursor::new(&frames_data)).unwrap();\n        let mut frames = Vec::new();\n        while let Some(f) = reader.next_frame().unwrap() {\n            frames.push(f);\n        }\n\n        let summary = process_frames(&client, &frames);\n        assert_eq!(summary.skipped_not_for_us, 1);\n        assert_eq!(summary.imported, 0);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_import_idempotent() {\n        let alice = Identity::generate();\n        let env = make_test_envelope(&alice);\n\n        let storage = Storage::open(\":memory:\").unwrap();\n        let client = Client::new(alice, Arc::new(NoopTransport), storage);\n\n        let frames_data = make_bundle_bytes(&[&env]);\n\n        // Import twice\n        for _ in 0..2 {\n            let mut reader = BundleReader::open(Cursor::new(&frames_data)).unwrap();\n            let mut frames = Vec::new();\n            while let Some(f) = reader.next_frame().unwrap() {\n                frames.push(f);\n            }\n            let _summary = process_frames(&client, &frames);\n        }\n        // Should not panic or error — idempotent\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_tombstone_frames_skipped() {\n        use reme_message::tombstone::SignedAckTombstone;\n        use reme_message::MessageID;\n\n        let alice = Identity::generate();\n        let tombstone = SignedAckTombstone::new(\n            MessageID::new(),\n            [42u8; 16],\n            &alice.x25519_secret().to_bytes(),\n        );\n        let wire = WirePayload::AckTombstone(tombstone);\n        let frame = wire.encode().unwrap();\n\n        let mut buf = Vec::new();\n        let mut writer = BundleWriter::new(&mut buf);\n        writer.write_frame(&frame).unwrap();\n        writer.finish().unwrap();\n\n        let mut reader = BundleReader::open(Cursor::new(&buf)).unwrap();\n        let mut frames = Vec::new();\n        while let Some(f) = reader.next_frame().unwrap() {\n            frames.push(f);\n        }\n\n        let storage = Storage::open(\":memory:\").unwrap();\n        let client = Client::new(alice, Arc::new(NoopTransport), storage);\n\n        let summary = process_frames(&client, &frames);\n        assert_eq!(summary.skipped_tombstones, 1);\n        assert_eq!(summary.imported, 0);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNote: The test for `test_import_self_addressed_messages` uses dummy envelopes with zero ephemeral keys — the decryption will fail inside `process_message_local` because the ECDH is invalid. The test verifies routing key dispatch works (not for us vs errors). A full round-trip test with real encryption would need `encrypt_to_mik` which is more complex — defer to integration tests.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Wire import into main.rs**\n\nIn `apps/client/src/main.rs`, add `mod import;` after `mod identity;`, and replace the import stub:\n\n```rust\nSome(Commands::Import(ref args)) => import::run_import(&config, args),\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Check if `async-trait` is available in client deps**\n\nThe `Transport` trait uses `#[async_trait]`. Check `apps/client/Cargo.toml` for `async-trait`. If not present, add it:\n\n```toml\nasync-trait = { workspace = true }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Verify everything compiles and tests pass**\n\nRun: `cargo fmt --all -- --check`\nRun: `cargo clippy -p client --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\nRun: `cargo test -p client`\nExpected: All pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/client/src/import.rs apps/client/src/main.rs apps/client/Cargo.toml\ngit commit -m \"feat: implement reme import command\n\nImport messages from .reme bundle files. Self-addressed messages are\ndecrypted and stored. Messages for other routing keys are skipped.\nDuplicate import is idempotent. Tombstone frames are counted but\nskipped (no client-side processing in v0.5).\n\nCloses #158\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Full workspace verification\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Run workspace-wide tests**\n\nRun: `cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`\nExpected: All pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run clippy**\n\nRun: `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\nExpected: Clean\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run fmt**\n\nRun: `cargo fmt --all -- --check`\nExpected: Clean\n",
